334th Candlelight Rally in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 30 (KCNA) -- The 334th candlelight rally demanding overall revision of SOFA, denouncing the U.S. for forcing troop dispatch and urging withdrawal of the humiliating decision on troop dispatch was reportedly held in front of Kwanghwamun in Seoul on October 25.
 Participating in the rally were more than 500 members of the All-People Measure Committee for Sin Hyo Sun and Sim Mi Son, Schoolgirls Killed by a U.S. Armored Car and the Emergency People's Action against Additional Troop Dispatch to Iraq and students under the south Korean Federation of University Student Councils. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the rally speakers stressed that troop dispatch to Iraq is the action of driving young people out to death and, at the same time, a crime of murdering Iraqi people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They called for blocking the troop dispatch on the strength of candlelight, saying that if troops are dispatched, all of Koreans should feel resp

Drop of U.S. Hostile Policy toward DPRK Demanded 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 30 (KCNA) -- The South Headquarters of the National Alliance of Youth and Students for the Country's Reunification on Oct. 26 issued a statement titled "U.S. should be well aware that there is no other way but to abandon its hostile policy toward north Korea."
 The statement said that the U.S. persistent war moves against the DPRK would never succeed as it has a strong ideological principle and its people are singleheartedly united and it has by powerful anti-imperialist independent forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We fully support the north's stand from the national viewpoint, the statement said, noting that the Korean nation will grow stronger in its anti-U.S. resistance and the north's nuclear deterrent will be proven in practice unless Bush drops his hostile policy toward north Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Bush should know well that all the Koreans approve the north's increase of its nuclear deterrent force, the statement stressed.

Epic in Praise of Songun Policy Written by Russian Poet 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 30 (KCNA) -- A Russian poet Alexandr Brezhnev created and published an epic "March for Victory of Songun".
 The epic said that leader Kim Jong Il started a grand long march for Songun, holding aloft the banner of justice, adding that the Songun policy pursued by the DPRK serves as treasured sword to win sure victory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that its army has brought joy and happiness to all the families of the country, the epic described the Songun policy as the strongest power that helped the DPRK stand on its own feet and a source of world-startling creation and construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The banner of Songun not only contributes to ensuring peace in Korea but serves as a shield to protect the security of our planet and ever-victorious lightning and thunder to wipe out all the rogues, it stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Praising Kim Jong Il as a generalissimo of peace as he champions world security with the Songun policy, the epic called for fighting to protect the sacred banner of Songun.

Rodong Sinmun on Immutable Idea of Korean Nation 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 30 (KCNA) -- The Korean nation has become convinced through the struggle in a little more than 3 years after the adoption of the historic June 15 North-South Joint Declaration that the idea of "By our nation itself" is, indeed, a great banner and an unchangeable idea which all the fellow countrymen in the north and the south of Korea should hold high in the struggle for independent reunification, says Rodong Sinmun in a signed article today.
 The article further says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The basic spirit of the declaration is "By our nation itself" and this idea is a motive force that enables the Korean nation to fulfil its responsibility and role in the reunification movement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This idea is full of pride in the character of the homogeneous nation with a time-honored history and the spirit of national independence to achieve independent reunification by the united efforts of the nation itself. It is a hard fact that the frozen minds melted in a moment after 50 odd years and the blood and terrestrial veins of the nation are being connected into one thanks to the idea. All the Koreans should regard it as the greatest honor to contribute to reunification and plunge themselves into the vast flow toward independent reunification to dedicate to the cause of reunification their utmost energy, ability and talent. Then the driving force of reunification will grow a hundred times stronger and the internal force for the cause of the country's reunification will gain in strength beyond measure. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The idea is a source of revitalization of the reunification movement. This is proved by the dramatic events that have occurred in the reunification movement waged by all the compatriots in both parts of the country under the uplifted banner of "By our nation itself." The inter-Korean relations which had remained in confrontation for more than half a century are now being converted into relations of "By our nation itself," the relations of cooperation.. The substantial reunification process is being accelerated through dialogues and contacts in various fields, political, economic and cultural, including the north-south ministerial talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Today the idea of "By our nation itself" serves as the banner of the country's reunification, the guiding pole of victory, as it inspires the reunification movement while fully displaying its validity and vitality.

Japan Hit for Toeing U.S. Line 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 30 (KCNA) -- Japan has quite often heard the international public call it a "stooge" and a "political dwarf" of the United States for zealously toeing the U.S. line. 
Despite this bitter insult from the international community Japan has not yet dropped a bad habit of toeing the U.S. line. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Commenting on this, Rodong Sinmun today in a signed commentary says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What matters is that this zealous pro-U.S. policy of Japan is reckless as it is driving the situation on the Korean peninsula to the brink of war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Not a few countries are guarding against their involvement in the U.S. moves or reluctant to favour them. But it is only Japan that gets zealous in supporting the U.S. moves to lay an international siege to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Branding Japan's act as a dangerous move to build in Asia a structure of confrontation between the DPRK and Asian countries led by the U.S. and Japan, the commentary observes: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Japan is bringing disgrace to itself as a dialogue partner by zealously supporting the U.S. moves against the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK bitterly dislikes to deal with those countries which blindly follow a big country, reading its face, bereft of their own view. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan's reckless act of toeing the U.S. line will bring nothing but disgrace and isolation to Japan.

KCNA Report on Japanese's Attempted Drug Smuggling 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 30 (KCNA) -- The KCNA today released the following report:
 Yoshiaki Sawada, department director of the Enterprise Co. Ltd. of Japan, is now under investigation by a competent institution for his attempted drug smuggling in violation of the DPRK laws and international law. He had entered the DPRK on Oct. 14 under the pretext of trade. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The preliminary results of the investigation confirmed that he planned to bribe a north Korean into buying drugs from a third country and smuggle them into Japan on board "Mangyongbong-92" at the instruction of his "master." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This case occurred at a time when the hostile forces in Japan are calling for checking the ship's call at the Japanese port, dubbing it a "ship for illegal remittance", "ship transporting missile parts" and "spy ship" in a bid to push the DPRK-Japan relations to the worst state. Clear is the political purpose sought through the case. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He will be sternly dealt with by a relevant law when the truth of the case is proved.

New Mushroom-Cultivating Technology
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 30 (KCNA) -- The Mushroom Institute under the Academy of Sciences of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea has made new inventions for cultivating mushroom and thus made it possible to industrialize the mushroom production.
 Researchers of the institute made ferment substances by using domestic animals' excrements, with which they made nutritive substratum for cultivating active and productive spores. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This method can be easily introduced anywhere. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They, basing themselves on the study of changes of temperature and humidity and the distribution density of various germs in each season, also invented a new technology of sorting out species of mushroom according to temperature and a method of cultivating mushroom step by step, irrespective of seasons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The valuable technology won a patent and was registered as an advanced farming technology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
It has already been introduced in a number of farms.

National Meeting of Scientists and Technicians Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 30 (KCNA) -- A national meeting of scientists and technicians was held here on Oct. 29 and 30.
 The meeting reviewed the performance of the last 5-year plan for the development of science and technology and discussed tasks and ways to thoroughly carry out the new 5-year plan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the meeting were leading officials of the Party and the state including Pak Pong Ju, Jon Pyong Ho and Han Song Ryong and functionaries concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Read out at the meeting was a congratulatory message sent by the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea to the participants in the meeting. The message recalled that the scientists and technicians had greatly helped the country tide over grim tests and vigorously advance toward the peak of a great prosperous powerful nation by successfully solving scientific and technological problems arising in strengthening national defences and boosting the national economy. Noting that it is the unshakable will of the WPK to carry the revolutionary cause of Juche to accomplishment, holding fast to science and technology together with the arms, the message called on all the scientists and technicians to work energetically to bring about a great heyday of scientific and technological development under the Songun revolutionary leadership of the Party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pyon Yong Rip, president of the Academy of Sciences, made a report at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Leader Kim Jong Il, pursuing great Songun politics, stipulated science and technology as one of three pillars for building a great prosperous powerful nation together with ideology and the arms and set forth the line of attaching importance to science and technology as a strategic line of building the great prosperous powerful socialist nation, he said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the main task of the new 5-year plan for scientific and technological development embodying the WPK's line of attaching importance to science and technology to rapidly develop ultra-modern science and technology, lift the science and technology of the country to the advanced level of the world and vigorously promote the technical restructuring and modernization of the national economy in conformity with the demand of the line of building economy in the Songun era. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is important in developing the country's science and technology to conduct brisk scientific and technological exchange and information services to introduce modern science and technology of other countries along with researches and development of new science and technology, the reporter stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made at the meeting. The speakers evinced their resolution to turn the motherland into a world-level power of science and technology by making a great leap in the development of science and technology in the revolutionary soldier spirit and the revolutionary spirit of self-reliance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They said they would cherish the WPK's idea of attaching importance to the military affairs as their firm faith and actively contribute to consolidating the defenses of the country as firm as a rock by preferentially solving the scientific and technological problems arising in the development of the defense industry as required by the line of building the socialist economy in the Songun era.

Wu Bangguo Visits Friendship Tower
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 30 (KCNA) -- The Chinese state delegation led by Wu Bangguo, member of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China and chairman of the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress of the People's Republic of China, laid a wreath before the Friendship Tower today.
 Present at the wreath-laying ceremony were Chinese Ambassador E.P. to the DPRK Wu Donghe and embassy officials. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also on hand were Kim Su Hak, minister of Public Health who is chairman of the Central Committee of the DPRK-China Friendship Association, and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A guard of honor of the three services of the Korean People's Army lined up before the tower. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Amid the playing of the wreath-laying music a wreath in the name of Wu Bangguo was laid before the tower. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Written on the ribbon of the wreath were letters reading "Martyrs of the Chinese People's Volunteers Will Be Immortal." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants observed a moment's silence in memory of the martyrs of the CPV who fell while bravely fighting in the Korean war against the U.S. imperialist aggressors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Wu Bangguo wrote in the visitor's book that Sino-Korean friendship will be everlasting.

List of Koreans Forcibly Drafted Obtained
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 30 (KCNA) -- The DPRK Measure Committee for Demanding Compensation to Comfort Women for the Japanese Army and Victims of Forcible Drafting recently obtained a list of 427,129 Korean victims who were forcibly drafted during the Japanese imperialists' military occupation of Korea.
 This is the result of the survey and discovery made by the fact-finding group for forcible drafting of Koreans active in Japan in the north and south of Korea, Japan, the United States and other areas since 1972. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The list includes some victims who were drafted for forced labor and conscription and as "volunteers' corps for labour", "comfort women" for the Japanese army, etc. before and after the outbreak of the Pacific war and those victims of the sunken "Ukishimamaru" and A-bomb victims among the more than 8.4 million Koreans who were forcibly drafted by the Japanese imperialists in the past. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They were drafted to various areas of Korea, all parts of Japan including Hokkaido and Hyogo, Fukuoka, Nagasaki, Saga, Hiroshima and Akita prefectures and overseas regions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Clarified in the list are the names of victims, the date of their birth, their domicile of origin and the places where they were drafted, the date of their death and so on. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The list will be very instrumental in probing the truth behind the unethical forcible drafting of Koreans committed by the Japanese imperialists in the past and will help the bereaved families of the victims confirm what actually happened in that period to their families and relatives from whom they have not heard for over half a century.

Homage Paid to Kim Il Sung
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 30 (KCNA) -- A Chinese state delegation led by Wu Bangguo, member of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China and chairman of the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress of China, visited the Kumsusan Memorial Palace on Oct. 30 to pay homage to President Kim Il Sung.
 Present there were Wu Donghe, Chinese ambassador to the DPRK, and staff members of the embassy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also present there were Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, Kwak Pom Gi, vice-premier of the DPRK Cabinet, Kim Su Hak, minister of Public Health who is chairman of the Central Committee of the DPRK-China Friendship Association, Kim Thae Jong, vice department director of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, Kim Yong Il, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs, and Choe Jin Su, DPRK ambassador e. p. to China. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A floral basket in the name of Wu Bangguo was laid before the statue of Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Written on the ribbon of the floral basket were letters "President Kim Il Sung is immortal." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants paid tribute to the statue of the President and made bows in humble reverence to the President who lies in state. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then they looked round with deep emotion the orders, medals and certificates of honorary titles he received at home and from different countries of the world, the Mourning Hall that reminds them of those days when the Korean people and the progressive people of the world bitterly grieved over the loss of the great father of the nation and the distinguished great man in the era of independence and a train car and a car he used during his on-the-spot guidance and foreign visits and in the last period of his life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Wu Bangguo made the following entry in the visitor's book: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
"Comrade President Kim Il Sung's revolutionary feats will remain long with the century."

Chinese State Delegation Visits Heavy Machine Complex
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 30 (KCNA) -- The state delegation of China led by Wu Bangguo, member of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China and chairman of the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress of the People's Republic of China, visited the Taean Heavy Machine Complex today.
 It was accompanied by Kim Su Hak, minister of Public Health who is chairman of the Central Committee of the DPRK-China Friendship Association, and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They were warmly greeted at the complex by Ri Kil Chun, vice-chairman of the Nampho City People's Committee, senior officials and employees of the complex. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They went round various production processes, being briefed on the fact that the complex has greatly contributed to developing the national economy as the country's leading heavy machine producer.

DPRK and China Discuss Nuclear Issue
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 30 (KCNA) -- The DPRK and Chinese sides discussed the nuclear issue between the DPRK and the U.S. while the Chinese state delegation is staying in the DPRK.
 The following is the results of the discussion: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Both sides supported a negotiated peaceful solution to the nuclear issue between the DPRK and the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 To this end both sides agreed in principle to pursue the course of the six-way talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK side expressed its willingness to take part in the future talks if they provide a process of putting into practice the proposal for a package solution based on the principle of simultaneous actions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Chinese side underscored the need to simultaneously clear up the concerns of the DPRK-U.S. sides without fail.

Kim Jong Il Receives Chinese State Delegation
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 30 (KCNA) -- Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea, chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission and supreme commander of the Korean People's Army, today received the Chinese state delegation led by Wu Bangguo, member of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China and chairman of the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress of the People's Republic of China, on an official goodwill visit to the DPRK.
 Present there were Member of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China and Vice-Premier of the State Council Zeng Peiyan, Vice-Chairman and Secretary General of the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress Sheng Huaren, Vice-Chairman of the Foreign Affairs Committee of the National People's Congress Lu Congmin, Vice-Minister of Foreign Affairs Wang Yi, Vice-Minister of Commerce Yu Guangzhou, Deputy Head of the International Liaison Department of the CPC Central Committee Liu Hongcai, Deputy Chief of the General Staff of the Chinese People's Liberation Army Ge Zhenfeng and Chinese Ambassador e.p. to the DPRK Wu Donghe. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand was Kang Sok Ju, first vice-minister of Foreign Affairs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the occasion Wu Bangguo conveyed the warm regards of Hu Jintao, general secretary of the Central Committee of the CPC and president of the PRC, and Jiang Zemin, chairman of the Central Military Commission, to Kim Jong Il and presented him with his own gift. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il thanked for this and extended his regards to Hu Jintao and Jiang Zemin. Then he conversed with Wu Bangguo in an amicable atmosphere. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il hosted a dinner in honor of the guests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were the members of the delegation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Kim Yong Chun, member of the DPRK National Defence Commission and chief of the General Staff of the KPA, Kang Sok Ju, first vice-minister of Foreign Affairs, Kim Yong Il, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs, and Choe Jin Su, DPRK ambassador e.p. to the PRC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The dinner proceeded in an amicable atmosphere.
